thickness, larger cup-to-disc ratio, and higher visual field pattern standard 
deviation) separated participants at high and low risk of developing POAG.
CONCLUSIONS: Clinicians and patients can make evidence-based decisions about the 
management of ocular hypertension using the risk model and considering patient 
age, medical status, life expectancy, and personal preference.

