BACKGROUND: The progress of medicine, science, technology, education, and 
culture improves, year by year, quality of life and life expectancy of the 
populace. The modern human has a chance to further improve the quality and 
duration of his/her life and the lives of his/her loved ones by bringing their 
lifestyle in line with their sequenced individual genomes. With this in mind, 
one of genome-based developments at the junction of personalized medicine and 
bioinformatics will be considered in this work, where we used two Web services: 
(i) SNP_TATA_Comparator to search for alleles with a single nucleotide 
